{"article_id":"WnfEzzZw0nGYM3ti","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Supreme Court 's Arizona Ruling Could Aid Obama","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"While Vexing Romney","depth":2},{"id":2,"text":"The political impact of Monday 's Supreme Court ruling","depth":10},{"id":3,"text":"that three of four provisions of Arizona 's immigration enforcement law are unconstitutional","depth":11},{"id":4,"text":"- and that a fourth could eventually be found to be -","depth":11},{"id":5,"text":"certainly appeared , at first blush , to be a significant political win for President Obama .","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"The Obama administration , after all , had challenged Arizona 's controversial SB 1070 legislation as usurping the federal government 's power","depth":11},{"id":7,"text":"to enforce the nation 's immigration laws ,","depth":11},{"id":8,"text":"a stance","depth":11},{"id":9,"text":"the high court mostly agreed with .","depth":11},{"id":10,"text":"Because many Latinos and immigrant-rights groups found the Arizona law to be repellent","depth":11},{"id":11,"text":"owing to features","depth":12},{"id":12,"text":"they feared","depth":13},{"id":13,"text":"would encourage racial profiling and discrimination ,","depth":13},{"id":14,"text":"that the Obama administration sided with them","depth":11},{"id":15,"text":"had already helped the president deepen his support with Hispanic voters .","depth":11},{"id":16,"text":"The 5-3 decision from a conservative court","depth":11},{"id":17,"text":"in which Chief Justice John Roberts joined the majority","depth":11},{"id":18,"text":"only strengthens the president 's argument","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"that he was right ,","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"and Arizona officials wrong on an issue with special significance to a key bloc of voters","depth":12},{"id":21,"text":"- Latinos -","depth":12},{"id":22,"text":"whose support he is counting on for re-election .","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"For the same reason , the Supreme Court decision seemingly complicates the political picture for Mitt Romney , the all-but-official Republican presidential nominee .","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"Romney ,","depth":12},{"id":25,"text":"who took a hard-line immigration stance during the Republican primaries ,","depth":12},{"id":26,"text":"has been forced to try to walk the tightrope","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"between appealing to conservatives","depth":12},{"id":28,"text":"wanting tougher enforcement","depth":12},{"id":29,"text":"while at the same time doing what he can","depth":13},{"id":30,"text":"to keep the wide gap in Latino support","depth":14},{"id":31,"text":"that exists between him and the president","depth":14},{"id":32,"text":"from getting any wider .","depth":12},{"id":33,"text":"The statements","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"issued by both Obama and Romney","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"captured the differences in their situations .","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"Obama welcomed the Supreme Court decision","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"and vowed","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"that his administration would police Arizona 's use of the so-called papers-please provision","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"the court upheld .","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"That provision requires Arizona police to inquire about the immigration status of people","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"stopped for other causes","depth":12},{"id":42,"text":"if the police have reason","depth":12},{"id":43,"text":"to suspect someone 's immigration status .","depth":12},{"id":44,"text":"Obama said :","depth":6},{"id":45,"text":"`` I am pleased","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"that the Supreme Court has struck down key provisions of Arizona 's immigration law .","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"What this decision makes unmistakably clear is that Congress must act on comprehensive immigration reform .","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"A patchwork of state laws is not a solution to our broken immigration system","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"- it 's part of the problem . `","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"` At the same time , I remain concerned about the practical impact of the remaining provision of the Arizona law","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"that requires local law enforcement officials to check the immigration status of anyone","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"they even suspect","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"to be here illegally .","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"I agree with the Court","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"that individuals can not be detained","depth":12},{"id":56,"text":"solely to verify their immigration status .","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"No American should ever live under a cloud of suspicion","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"just because of what they look like .","depth":12},{"id":59,"text":"Going forward , we must ensure","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"that Arizona law enforcement officials do not enforce this law in a manner","depth":12},{"id":61,"text":"that undermines the civil rights of Americans ,","depth":12},{"id":62,"text":"as the Court 's decision recognizes ... ''","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"In his statement , Romney blasted the president","depth":6},{"id":64,"text":"but did not specifically say","depth":7},{"id":65,"text":"whether he agreed with the Supreme Court 's ruling :","depth":7},{"id":66,"text":"`` Today 's decision underscores the need for a President","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"who will lead on this critical issue","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"and work in a bipartisan fashion","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"to pursue a national immigration strategy .","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"President Obama has failed to provide any leadership on immigration .","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"This represents yet another broken promise by this President .","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"I believe","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"that each state has the duty","depth":11},{"id":74,"text":"- and the right -","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"to secure our borders","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"and preserve the rule of law ,","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"particularly when the federal government has failed to meet its responsibilities .","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"As Candidate Obama , he promised to present an immigration plan during his first year in office .","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"But 4 years later , we are still waiting . ''","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"Gary Segura , a Stanford University political scientist , viewed the decision as a decidedly mixed one for Latinos ,","depth":7},{"id":81,"text":"since the most repugnant part of the law to them , police inquiries into immigration status , survived .","depth":7},{"id":82,"text":"But he saw the decision as having substantial benefits for Obama ,","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"giving the president the best of both worlds :","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"`` I think","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"it 's a huge win for two reasons .","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"First , losing on that one provision is very likely to mobilize voters .","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"The threat is still there ;","depth":12},{"id":88,"text":"the threat is still meaningful .","depth":12},{"id":89,"text":"But the president and his administration intervened on behalf of Latinos","depth":12},{"id":90,"text":"and defeated three of the four provisions . ... `` And of course Gov . Romney and the Republicans embrace the part of the law","depth":13},{"id":91,"text":"that was upheld .","depth":13},{"id":92,"text":"So the president can go to Latino voters","depth":12},{"id":93,"text":"and say ,","depth":13},{"id":94,"text":"' I had your back .","depth":16},{"id":95,"text":"I sued on [ your ] behalf ...","depth":16},{"id":96,"text":"I got three out of four of them overturned .","depth":15},{"id":97,"text":"But there 's still a threat","depth":15},{"id":98,"text":"since Republicans think","depth":16},{"id":99,"text":"it 's such a great idea . '","depth":16},{"id":100,"text":"So , politically , I think","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"it 's a huge win for the administration . ''","depth":10},{"id":102,"text":"Charles Foster , a prominent Houston immigration lawyer , thinks","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"the Supreme Court decision did n't do Romney any favors .","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"Foster , by the way , has been a bipartisan immigration-policy adviser , first to George W. Bush in 2000 and 2003 , then to Obama in 2008 .","depth":9},{"id":105,"text":"He also filed a friend-of-the-court brief","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"supporting the Justice Department 's challenge of the Arizona law .","depth":10},{"id":107,"text":"`` This decision puts more pressure on Gov . Romney than on President Obama .","depth":8},{"id":108,"text":"The Obama administration has been criticized for having challenged the Arizona law in the Supreme Court ,","depth":11},{"id":109,"text":"but here you have a fairly conservative court","depth":12},{"id":110,"text":"by and large upholding Obama 's position","depth":15},{"id":111,"text":"that this is a federal issue . `` On the other hand , Gov . Romney ,","depth":15},{"id":112,"text":"I think ,","depth":14},{"id":113,"text":"in ways","depth":15},{"id":114,"text":"that did n't really reflect his true beliefs ,","depth":15},{"id":115,"text":"tactically took hard positions during the primary .","depth":14},{"id":116,"text":"He wound up taking the position","depth":11},{"id":117,"text":"that adopting Arizona-type laws was a good thing for the states to do .","depth":11},{"id":118,"text":"`` This decision will put him in the potentially awkward position","depth":10},{"id":119,"text":"of having to say","depth":11},{"id":120,"text":"that as president he would seek federal approval","depth":12},{"id":121,"text":"to do precisely what the Supreme Court has struck down . ''","depth":12},{"id":122,"text":"Not everyone thought","depth":10},{"id":123,"text":"that Romney would necessarily have to play defense after the high court decision .","depth":10},{"id":124,"text":"Did Romney need to distance himself from the Arizona law","depth":10},{"id":125,"text":"or revise his rhetoric ?","depth":10},{"id":126,"text":"Scott Cottington , a Minnesota-based Republican consultant and former political director for the National Republican Senatorial Committee was asked :","depth":10},{"id":127,"text":"`` No , not necessarily . `` It seems to me","depth":12},{"id":128,"text":"that","depth":14},{"id":129,"text":"if a candidate for national office makes statements in support of federalism , and the rights of states","depth":17},{"id":130,"text":"to do things","depth":17},{"id":131,"text":"even if turned back by the Supreme Court ,","depth":16},{"id":132,"text":"that 's a good thing .","depth":15},{"id":133,"text":"States try things ,","depth":16},{"id":134,"text":"the Supreme Court rules ,","depth":16},{"id":135,"text":"and there 's more clarity .","depth":15},{"id":136,"text":"I tend to think","depth":16},{"id":137,"text":"that indicates","depth":16},{"id":138,"text":"the process is working . `` What Romney needs to do over the next four of five months , I do n't know .","depth":15},{"id":139,"text":"I do know","depth":12},{"id":140,"text":"that you ca n't outpander Obama . ''","depth":12},{"id":141,"text":"Romney 's statement provides some clues","depth":12},{"id":142,"text":"about what he is likely to continue doing","depth":13},{"id":143,"text":"to undermine the president 's approval ratings with Latino voters .","depth":13},{"id":144,"text":"That is to point out that Obama ,","depth":13},{"id":145,"text":"who promised comprehensive immigration reform legislation as a presidential candidate in 2008 ,","depth":13},{"id":146,"text":"has failed to deliver .","depth":12},{"id":147,"text":"As Segura said :","depth":12},{"id":148,"text":"`` What he is trying to do is accentuate the president 's failures on immigration","depth":13},{"id":149,"text":"which are there ,","depth":15},{"id":150,"text":"which are meaningful","depth":15},{"id":151,"text":"and which , prior to a week ago ,","depth":16},{"id":152,"text":"I think","depth":16},{"id":153,"text":"were a real drag on the enthusiasm of Latino voters . ''","depth":15},{"id":154,"text":"That was an allusion to the president 's announcement","depth":13},{"id":155,"text":"that he would essentially implement parts of the DREAM Act legislation","depth":14},{"id":156,"text":"stalled in Congress .","depth":14},{"id":157,"text":"Besides deferring deportation proceedings for some young illegal immigrants","depth":14},{"id":158,"text":"brought to the U.S. by their parents ,","depth":14},{"id":159,"text":"the president 's move would also allow such immigrants to get work or student visas .","depth":13},{"id":160,"text":"Segura said :","depth":10},{"id":161,"text":"`` What he 's not saying ,","depth":12},{"id":162,"text":"and what every Latino voter already knows","depth":13},{"id":163,"text":"if they pay attention to Jorge Ramos or any Spanish-language media or for that matter , English-language media ,","depth":13},{"id":164,"text":"is that the obstacle for immigration reform has been and continues to be the Republican Congress . ``","depth":11},{"id":165,"text":"You 'll notice","depth":12},{"id":166,"text":"that the statement does n't have any immigration policy in it .","depth":12},{"id":167,"text":"It 's not the case","depth":14},{"id":168,"text":"that Romney 's promising to deport less people .","depth":14},{"id":169,"text":"It 's not the case","depth":14},{"id":170,"text":"that Romney 's arguing for going beyond the president 's suspension of deportation for DREAM-eligible kids .","depth":14},{"id":171,"text":"It 's none of the above ,","depth":12},{"id":172,"text":"and he sides with Arizona .","depth":12},{"id":173,"text":"Arizona has the right","depth":14},{"id":174,"text":"to defend its borders .","depth":14},{"id":175,"text":"So I think","depth":14},{"id":176,"text":"that has very little effect .","depth":14},{"id":177,"text":"They 're trying to thread the needle","depth":12},{"id":178,"text":"and they 're not going to do it . ''","depth":12},{"id":179,"text":"Still ,","depth":9},{"id":180,"text":"while unpopular with many Latino voters ,","depth":11},{"id":181,"text":"the Arizona law has many supporters in the rest of the electorate .","depth":11},{"id":182,"text":"A recent Pew Research Center poll found","depth":12},{"id":183,"text":"that a solid majority of voters , 58 percent , supported the law","depth":13},{"id":184,"text":"while 38 percent did n't .","depth":13},{"id":185,"text":"True , that level of support was down from the 64 percent","depth":13},{"id":186,"text":"who two years ago said","depth":14},{"id":187,"text":"they approved it ,","depth":14},{"id":188,"text":"but it was still a substantial majority .","depth":12},{"id":189,"text":"Updated at 6:08 pm -","depth":6},{"id":190,"text":"Romney spokesman Rick Gorka had an exchange with reporters on the Romney plane Monday","depth":8},{"id":191,"text":"did little","depth":9},{"id":192,"text":"to shed much light on the candidate 's views .","depth":9},{"id":193,"text":"An excerpt from Politico.com :","depth":8},{"id":194,"text":"GORKA :","depth":9},{"id":195,"text":"`` The governor supports the states ' rights","depth":12},{"id":196,"text":"to craft immigration laws","depth":12},{"id":197,"text":"when the federal government has failed to do so .","depth":11},{"id":198,"text":"This president promised as a candidate to address immigration in his first year","depth":11},{"id":199,"text":"and has n't ,","depth":12},{"id":200,"text":"and waited actually 'til four and a half months before the election","depth":13},{"id":201,"text":"to put in place a stopgap measure . ''","depth":13},{"id":202,"text":"QUESTION :","depth":8},{"id":203,"text":"So does he think","depth":9},{"id":204,"text":"it 's wrongly decided ?","depth":9},{"id":205,"text":"GORKA :","depth":8},{"id":206,"text":"`` The governor supports the states ' rights","depth":10},{"id":207,"text":"to do this .","depth":10},{"id":208,"text":"It 's a 10th amendment issue . ''","depth":9},{"id":209,"text":"QUESTION :","depth":9},{"id":210,"text":"So he thinks","depth":10},{"id":211,"text":"it 's constitutional ?","depth":10},{"id":212,"text":"GORKA :","depth":9},{"id":213,"text":"`` The governor believes","depth":10},{"id":214,"text":"the states have the rights","depth":12},{"id":215,"text":"to craft their own immigration laws ,","depth":12},{"id":216,"text":"especially when the federal government has failed to do so . ''","depth":11},{"id":217,"text":"QUESTION :","depth":9},{"id":218,"text":"And what does he think about parts invalidated ?","depth":9},{"id":219,"text":"GORKA :","depth":10},{"id":220,"text":"`` What Arizona has done","depth":12},{"id":221,"text":"and other states have done is a direct result of the failure of this president","depth":12},{"id":222,"text":"to address illegal immigration .","depth":11},{"id":223,"text":"It 's within their rights to craft those laws and this debate ,","depth":10},{"id":224,"text":"and the Supreme Court ruling is a direct response of the president","depth":11},{"id":225,"text":"failing to address this issue . ''","depth":11},{"id":226,"text":"At an appearance in Scottsdale , AZ , Romney did go beyond his statement of earlier in the day .","depth":3},{"id":227,"text":"An excerpt from The Wall Street Journal","depth":4},{"id":228,"text":"which reported on what he said at a fundraiser :","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":457,"left":230,"right":456,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":230,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":456,"left":453,"right":455,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":453,"left":307,"right":452,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":307,"left":290,"right":306,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":290,"left":271,"right":289,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":271,"left":260,"right":270,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":260,"left":243,"right":259,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":243,"left":233,"right":242,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":233,"left":232,"right":5,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":232,"left":2,"right":231,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":231,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":242,"left":236,"right":241,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":236,"left":234,"right":235,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":234,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":235,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":241,"left":239,"right":240,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":239,"left":10,"right":238,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":238,"left":11,"right":237,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":237,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":240,"left":14,"right":15,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":259,"left":249,"right":258,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":249,"left":245,"right":248,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":245,"left":244,"right":18,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":244,"left":16,"right":17,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":248,"left":19,"right":247,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":247,"left":246,"right":22,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":246,"left":20,"right":21,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":258,"left":23,"right":257,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":257,"left":251,"right":256,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":251,"left":250,"right":26,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":250,"left":24,"right":25,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":256,"left":252,"right":255,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":252,"left":27,"right":28,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":255,"left":254,"right":32,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":254,"left":29,"right":253,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":253,"left":30,"right":31,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":270,"left":262,"right":269,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":262,"left":261,"right":35,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":261,"left":33,"right":34,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":269,"left":36,"right":268,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":268,"left":37,"right":267,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":267,"left":263,"right":266,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":263,"left":38,"right":39,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":266,"left":264,"right":265,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":264,"left":40,"right":41,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":265,"left":42,"right":43,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":289,"left":44,"right":288,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":288,"left":275,"right":287,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":275,"left":273,"right":274,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":273,"left":272,"right":47,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":272,"left":45,"right":46,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":274,"left":48,"right":49,"relation":"restatement","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":287,"left":278,"right":286,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":278,"left":50,"right":277,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":277,"left":276,"right":53,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":276,"left":51,"right":52,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":286,"left":282,"right":285,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":282,"left":54,"right":281,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":281,"left":279,"right":280,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":279,"left":55,"right":56,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":280,"left":57,"right":58,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":285,"left":59,"right":284,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":284,"left":283,"right":62,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":283,"left":60,"right":61,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":306,"left":292,"right":305,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":292,"left":63,"right":291,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":291,"left":64,"right":65,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":305,"left":297,"right":304,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":297,"left":295,"right":296,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":295,"left":66,"right":294,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":294,"left":67,"right":293,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":293,"left":68,"right":69,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":296,"left":70,"right":71,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":304,"left":302,"right":303,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":302,"left":72,"right":301,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":301,"left":299,"right":300,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":299,"left":298,"right":75,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":298,"left":73,"right":74,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":300,"left":76,"right":77,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":303,"left":78,"right":79,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":452,"left":415,"right":451,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":415,"left":328,"right":414,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":328,"left":308,"right":327,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":308,"left":80,"right":81,"relation":"explanation","nucl